   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" mid="9" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Gossip.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-d" mid="10" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Trouble with Merchant May.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-g" mid="11" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Being a loner.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Do I have any problem?<BR>Hmm I wonder what kind of problem I had?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" mid="23" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Well. There was some rumor back in my hometown that I am just a loner hermit who looked at Heraldry wholeday. Where did you hear that?<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey gets all sensitive. Merchant Maybe there really was a rumor like that.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" mid="24" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Let get the facts right.. I am not a loner hermit, it's just that I never step out of the house for about three years</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Do you understand the feeling of failing Heraldry scholar certificate exam three years in a row<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey lets out a sigh and starts pouring out his past sufferings. It appears that he went through quite a lot.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-e" mid="27" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Ah, so you know too?<BR>I wouldn't call it a trouble, but... you know how Merchant May started practicing singing because she wants to be like Ms. Adelynn?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-f" mid="28" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>It appears that some ignorant adventurer gave Merchant May a music sheet. Talk about giving harpies extra wings...<BR>This is an outrageous thing to do, its like giving an orc his shield back!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Since then, Merchant May keep singing non stop everyady and night, but that is if you call it singing.<FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey's face looks pale.)</FONT><BR>This is a serious problem, what can we do to stop her from singing, oh yes... she sing while cooking too!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-h" mid="29" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Hahaha. I'm not too concerned about that kind of stuff.<BR>It's not easy for a diligent scholar to take care of human relationships.<BR>Hahahaha.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>But Ms. Tiana told me this yesterday.<BR>Do I really not have a lover because of studies?<BR>What do you think she meant by that? Maybe Ms. Tiana is interested in me?<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Heraldry Scholar Bailey is concerned about something that's probably not true.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
